<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/29305619-allan-macleod"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/29305619-allan-macleod">Allan MacLeod</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Regarding the first part of your question: as somebody who had a few years of experience before the internet swallowed everything, my recommendation i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Regarding the first part of your question: as somebody who had a few years of experience before the internet swallowed everything, my recommendation is to get your book and isolate yourself in a library, cafe, or similar. Turn your phone on silent and leave it in your backpack while you read. Make regular meditation and mindfulness a habit so that you can take ten minutes to clear your mind of static when necessary.<br /><br />Also, I find that my e-reader is a more comfortable and ergonomically pleasing way to read (especially for heavier volumes) that ultimately reduces distractions while I read and lets me read longer, more often, and in more places.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
