<div id="review_4526063840" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4526063840" />
    <a title="Vince" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/128225739-vince"><img alt="Vince" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629724401p2/128225739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4526063840?book_show_action=true">Feb 03, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vince" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vince" href="/user/show/128225739-vince">Vince</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780544382046" href="/book/show/22749803-homage-to-catalonia">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4526063840" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1339574876074513099"><b>One of the most horrible features of war is that all the war-propaganda, all the screaming and lies and hatred, comes invariably from people who are not fighting.</b><br/><br/>Homage to Catalonia is Orwell&apos;s account of his experiences in The Spanish Civil War, a war of Fascism against the working class. He does his best to give an unbiased view on what happened and actually fought with the revolutionaries fighting for democracy. He suffered from food shortages, tedious guard duties and inclement weather durin</span>
  <span id="freeText1339574876074513099" style="display:none"><b>One of the most horrible features of war is that all the war-propaganda, all the screaming and lies and hatred, comes invariably from people who are not fighting.</b><br /><br />Homage to Catalonia is Orwell's account of his experiences in The Spanish Civil War, a war of Fascism against the working class. He does his best to give an unbiased view on what happened and actually fought with the revolutionaries fighting for democracy. He suffered from food shortages, tedious guard duties and inclement weather during his stay. I must admit, I was quite confused on the politics because politics frankly bore me and on the other hand so many names and factions were thrown at me, that I couldn't figure out who's who. It all felt so pointless and dull but luckily Orwell clears a lot of uncertainty in the Appendices at the back. It made for some admittedly dry reading but it did accomplish clearing up the confusion I had which was a relief. <br /><br />Orwell fought with the faction known as the POUM:(Partido Obrero Unificacion Marxista) and had many close scrapes including narrowly escaping arrest when the POUM was declared a Trotskyist faction secretly working for the fascists. The POUM believed that if the workers do not control the armed forces, the armed forces will control the workers. It's all very complicated and a great deal has gone over my head but I do know that the side Orwell was fighting for unfortunately lost which led to the inevitable takeover by Francisco Franco, leader of the Nationalist forces in Spain. On the whole, this was an informative and unique book but I did initially give it a low score because of boredom and confusion but thankfully the Appendices made matters clear.<br /><br /><b>In case I have not said this somewhere earlier in the book I will say it now: beware of my partisanship, my mistakes of fact and the distortion inevitably caused by my having seen only one corner of events. And beware of exactly the same things when you read any other book on this period of the Spanish war.</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="1339574876074513099" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


