        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4158773457" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6469109569092756785">“I have come to Spain to join the militia to fight against Fascism.”<br/><br/>This is Orwell’s rather humble chronicle of his participation in the Spanish Civil War. As a volunteer in the POUM militia, he fought in the trenches of Aragon and was an eyewitness to the 1937 May Days Uprising in Barcelona. <br/><br/>“Why can&apos;t we drop all this political nonsense and get on with the war?”<br/><br/>When Orwell writes of Catalonia, of being near-fatally wounded in the throat, of the bravery and sacrifice of his comrades, we see the</span>
  <span id="freeText6469109569092756785" style="display:none">“I have come to Spain to join the militia to fight against Fascism.”<br /><br />This is Orwell’s rather humble chronicle of his participation in the Spanish Civil War. As a volunteer in the POUM militia, he fought in the trenches of Aragon and was an eyewitness to the 1937 May Days Uprising in Barcelona. <br /><br />“Why can't we drop all this political nonsense and get on with the war?”<br /><br />When Orwell writes of Catalonia, of being near-fatally wounded in the throat, of the bravery and sacrifice of his comrades, we see the forging of his political outlook. We are privy to the genesis of “1984” and “Animal Farm.” <br /><br />"Every line of serious work that I have written since 1936 has been written, directly or indirectly, against totalitarianism and for democratic socialism, as I understand it."</span>
  <a data-text-id="6469109569092756785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
